  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(7) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "If ye had known me, ye should have known my Father also.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—The thought here is made quite plain by what has preceded; but the form in which it is expressed demands attention. The emphasis of the first part of the sentence is not upon “Me” as is generally supposed, but upon “known.” In the second part the emphatic words are “My Father.” The English word “known” represents two Greek words in the better text which are not identical in meaning. The former means, to know by observation, the latter to know by reflection. It is the difference between ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "connaître",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "savoir;",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " between ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "kennen",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (ken, k(e)now), and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "wissen",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (wit, wisdom). We may express the meaning more exactly thus, “If ye had ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "recognised",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Me, ye would have known ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "My Father",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " also.” If ye had recognised who I really am; ye would have known that I and My Father are one.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And from henceforth ye know him, and have seen him.—Comp. John 13:31, where the glorifying of the Son of Man is regarded as in the future which is immediately present. He can, therefore, say that from this time onwards, after the full declaration of Himself in John 14:6; John 14:9 et seq., they know and have seen the Father.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "And from henceforth ye know him, and have seen him.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Comp. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "John 13:31",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", where the glorifying of the Son of Man is regarded as in the future which is immediately present. He can, therefore, say that from this time onwards, after the full declaration of Himself in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "John 14:6",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "John 14:9",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "et seq.,",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " they know and have seen the Father.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
