  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "John 14:7",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "John 14:7",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "If ye had known me ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— As ye might and ought to have known me. If ye had earnestly sought and obtained that knowledge of me which is communicated by the Spirit of wisdom and revelation, (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ephesians 1:17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ",) ye would ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "have known my Father also ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— In his various perfections, and in those blessed relations in which he stands to such as believe on Christ with a living faith, and are ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "accepted ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "through him, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the beloved. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "“If you had had an adequate idea of my character, from the miracles I have performed, and from the marks of goodness, justice, and wisdom, which have manifested themselves in my life and doctrine; you could not have been ignorant of my Father; because his attributes are the same.” ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And from henceforth ye know him, and have seen him — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "As it may be truly affirmed, considering the discoveries that I have made of him, and the manifestation of the divine perfections which you have seen in me.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
